value.0: Come to stare... Well I do not feel like being your mockery begone!

We are the Followers of Set. The other fools may refer to us at times as "Setites." We are mistrusted perhaps more than any other clan. Our ties with the archetypal Serpent of myth are well-known, and bolstered by our powers. When we enter a city, the Cainite power structure almost inevitably erodes. But most unnerving of all to other Cainites is that we share a dark and powerful faith as a clan -- a faith that the blood of gods pulses in our cold veins
Ahh the other clans... which would you care to know about.
They dislike us and spread slander against us, for they cannot accept that we are elder and of greater birth than they. Abide a while yet, and their rule will stop persecuting us soon enough.
Self-titled dragons who nonetheless drawl nightly on their bellies and feast on dust. They are crafty, but not so crafty as we.

How like a precious child, with spectacles perched so serious on his nose and a heavy book in his lap! Ah, but this little darling might eventually prove dangerous, and so requires a parent's gentle guidance...
Such ardor is...admirable. I could become drunk on a Toreador's passion, and might drain him dry trying to fill myself with it.

Concern yourself not with the wandering adolescents of this clan; they are foolish and ignorant of their true lineage. It is the head of the rakshasa that bears watching, and its eyes have opened again.
A not-so-subtle reminder of what we all are, and why it is pointless to play at anything else.

Dangerous. They are the keepers of truths perhaps even older than we. Fortunate that the other clans are foolish enough to dismiss the mad ones' prophesying as delusion and rambling; were they wise enough to listen, Set's time might well have come before we were ready.
Children of the voice, though still fresh from the other's teat and new-weaned on stolen vitae. Only rhe eldest among them have any idea of exactly what power they evoke.
Cunning in a savage sort of way, but lacking even the common sense of a wild dog. They have nothing we require, and are valuable only as an object lesson in control.
They have forogotten more lessons than they've learned. Once worth a touch of respect, now...nothing really.
It seems that our brothers have forgotten all their teachings at the merest taste of a drop of vitae. And what implications this has...
We usually organize ourselves into temples where we can exchange lore and practice our rites. Our hierarchy tends to be organized by age, with the eldest and wises among us officiating.
As creatures of the most ancient darkness, we have a severe allergy to bright lights of all sorts, and sunlight in particular.
We typically choose neonates from our own retainers. And tend to choose highly intelligent individuals to become members of our clan. Normally we make no distinction among race or nationality.

Celerity is a Discipline that grants vampires supernatural speed and finesse by expending vitae. Presence, the discipline of unnatural attraction and emotional control. This discipline is the ultimate exaltation of the "Power of personality" that many kindred have.Potence is Discipline that grants the vampires supernatural strength.

Many younger Setites aren't above snatching the most practical crashplaces possible, the elders treat the haven-building as a reverential process. Many use ancient alchemical rituals to consecrate their havens, be they temples, hidden libraries or simple crypts. Most train cadres of ghouls for the "scared duty" of guarding the master's haven, and some are fond of letting snakes roam the interior of their lairs. Those havens are often decorated in ancient Egyptian fashion.
